\section*{'Digital' Radiography}

Two types
- Computed radiography, called CR
- Uses existing equipment to make exposures
- Film cassette is replaced with a charged metal plate
- After exposure, plate is 'read in a special device
- Digital radiography, called DR
- Requires conversion of the entire x-ray room
- Film cassette is replaced by a CCD sensor (like in a d igital camera or video camera)

